<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":31194,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20200217022548/https://interactiveswingtrades.com/scandals/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://interactiveswingtrades.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-26-17-03-15-219-1-1024x640.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-31194"/></a></figure></div>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":39,"className":"cursive-background-image"} -->
<p style="font-size:39px" class="cursive-background-image">“The development of our financial oligarchy followed, in this respect, lines with which the <strong><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">history of political despotism</span> </em></strong>has familiarized us: usurpation,<strong><em> <span style="text-decoration: underline;">proceeding by gradual encroachment rather than by violent acts</span></em></strong>; subtle and often long-concealed concentration of distinct functions….<br><br>……<strong><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">which are beneficial when separately administered</span>, </em></strong>and dangerous only when combined in the same persons. <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>It was by processes such as these that Caesar Augustus became master of Rome</em>. <br></span><br>The makers of our own Constitution had in mind similar dangers to our political liberty when they<span style="text-decoration: underline;"> <strong><em>provided so carefully for the</em></strong></span> <em><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">separation of governmental powers</span></strong></em>”.<br><br><a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="(1914) Other People’s Money and How the Bankers Use It– Chapter I: Our Financial Oligarchy (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/FjfOR" target="_blank"><em>(1914) Other People’s Money and How the Bankers Use It– Chapter I: Our Financial Oligarchy</em></a><br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":31468,"width":507,"height":506,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img src="https://interactiveswingtrades.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2019-11-29-21-57-43-247.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-31468" width="507" height="506"/></figure></div>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>When you compare the structure of our financial markets to what was revealed in the Pujo Committee and the articles cited in the book, "Other People’s Money and How the Bankers Use It", you will quickly realize how little of a  difference there is between the anti competitive robber barons that existed during the early 20th century, and our capital markets today. <br><br>They own the banks; they own brokers; they own the financial news media; they own the <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="regulators (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.investmentnews.com/article/20180814/FREE/180819974/finra-panel-awards-clients-5-million-for-churning-but-from-defunct" target="_blank">regulators</a>; they own the clearing houses; they <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="control the government (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/vEa9V" target="_blank">control the government</a>; and worst of all, they block competition, even if offers new technology that could revolutionize entire industries. <br><br>But why should we be surprised by this?  As history has shown time and time again, "absolute power corrupts absolutely".<br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"align":"center"} -->
<p class="has-text-align-center"></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:olympus-google-fonts/google-fonts {"blockType":"h1","fontID":"helvetica","fontSize":48,"align":"center","content":"The Depository Trust and Clearing Corporation"} /-->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"blue-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="blue-yellow-background-link">Stock and bond clearing is exclusively owned and controlled by the biggest banks and brokers in America.  Simply put, Central Clearing is <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="the middleman that sits between a trade (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-2037.0-2079.31" target="_blank">the middleman that sits between a trade</a>, guaranteeing both the buyer and the seller receives their cash or securities.  If a buyer or seller fails to deliver the cash or securities, the clearing house guarantees delivery to the <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="counterparties  (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-2037.0-2079.31" target="_blank">counterparties </a>by making up for the loss with their own money.<br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":35492,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-12-04-33-52-712.jpg?fit=1024%2C409&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-35492"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><br><br>Without this essential service, a stock exchange will struggle to survive because nobody will be sure if the counterparty will deliver, and all it takes is the slightest bit of doubt for the entire system to collapse.   The exchange may be able to operate on a small scale, but not at the capacity  that you would expect to see on  the NASDAQ or NYSE, and if you have competitors -- and you always do -- bankruptcy is not just a possibility, but a certainty. <br><br>In the United States of America, there is only one central clearinghouse: <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="The Depository Trust and Clearing Corporation (opens in a new tab)" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Depository_Trust_%26_Clearing_Corporation" target="_blank">The Depository Trust and Clearing Corporation</a>, and for almost 50 years they have maintained a virtual monopoly over this essential service.  It is a private corporation owned by the major banks and brokerage houses.<br><br>The Federal Reserve Bank of New York shares many similarities.  It is the only institution that is legally sanctioned through the Federal Reserve Act to manipulate interest rates with what they refer to as <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Open Market Operations (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.investopedia.com/ask/answers/06/openmarketoperations.asp" target="_blank">Open Market Operations</a>, and it is also owned by the banks and brokers. </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>FINRA, their industry watchdog, is one of the only regulatory entities in America that, through its&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://archive.is/dMijU#selection-2729.0-2770.0" target="_blank">mandatory arbitration process</a>, is allowed to operate outside of common law — a judicial system that has been practiced in the western world since the early&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.britannica.com/topic/common-law" target="_blank">Middle Ages</a>.  It too is owned by the banks and brokers.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"red-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="red-yellow-background-link">This means if you are a client of Goldman Sachs, Morgan Stanley, Merrill Lynch, or any of the other major brokers in America, and you have evidence proving one of their 100's of thousands of employees has harmed you financially, you will be forced to sue them through a separate <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="arbitration process (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.investmentnews.com/article/20180814/FREE/180819974/finra-panel-awards-clients-5-million-for-churning-but-from-defunct" target="_blank">arbitration process</a> that they fund, that they control, and who's management they elect; all <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="outside of common law (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.investmentnews.com/article/20180814/FREE/180819974/finra-panel-awards-clients-5-million-for-churning-but-from-defunct" target="_blank">outside of common law</a>.  </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>As you can see in the screenshot pictured below, they own the only centralized clearinghouse in the country: The DTCC</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31153,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://archive.is/OGRnf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-27-17-00-32-252.jpg?fit=1024%2C466&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31153"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:olympus-google-fonts/google-fonts {"blockType":"h1","fontID":"helvetica","fontSize":44,"align":"center","content":"Blocking New Technology"} /-->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"red-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="red-yellow-background-link">Just to give you an idea of the influence these TBTF banks  have over these institutions, we are going to analyze a recent lawsuit filed by a consortium of pension funds against the largest banks and brokers in the United States.  It perfectly illustrates their <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-15375.6-15417.77" target="_blank">stranglehold over our capital markets</a>, proving beyond any shadow of a doubt that not only will these massive corporations work together behind closed doors to <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="stifle competition (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-2699.15-2717.97" target="_blank">stifle competition</a>, but they also have the ability to<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-18717.0-18729.10" target="_blank"> coerce the directors of the DTCC</a>  into blocking new entrants that pose a threat to <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-13613.7-13631.16" target="_blank">their hegemony</a>. <br><br>Before we go any further, it is important for you to understand that there is tremendous risk for those who post this online, and much of what you are about to see has been buried.  Don't be deterred by the length; about 60% of this article is screenshots, so it looks much longer than it actually is. <br><br>When you click on the image below, it will take you to the exact line of text.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":30991,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><a href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-18717.0-18729.10" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://interactiveswingtrades.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-26-16-31-31-028.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-30991"/></a></figure></div>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"blue-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="blue-yellow-background-link">There is probably no better example of their anti-competitive behavior than in the stock loan industry, where for the past <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="20 years (opens in a new tab)" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20070106082943/http://www.vodiagroup.com/pdfs/FourMyths.pdf" target="_blank">20 years</a>, pension funds, endowments, and mutual funds have all been <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="forced  (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-30827.4-30885.82" target="_blank">forced<em> </em></a>to use their services for lack of any viable alternative.<br><br>Most of the time, retirement funds tend to hold their investments long-term, and to take advantage of these dormant positions, fund managers will often attempt to increase their clients returns by loaning out your shares to short sellers and market makers so they can be used for arbitrage.  <br><br>There is one big problem, though: still to this day, there is no centralized exchange available for stock loans, which forces massive money managers like <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.secinfo.com/$/SEC/Manager.asp?CIK=1364742&amp;Sort=5#1stPage" target="_blank">Blackrock </a>and <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.secinfo.com/$/SEC/Manager.asp?CIK=919079&amp;Sort=5#1stPage" target="_blank">CalPERS </a>, along with <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://interactiveswingtrades.com/2019/12/28/q3-fund-activity-almost-complete/" target="_blank">every hedge fund in America </a>, to employ brokers to match borrowers and lenders, siphoning <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="$100's of billions (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-26655.0-26691.78" target="_blank">$100's of billions</a> from our retirement savings.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><br>Today, most of these transactions are <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="still facilitated over-the-counter (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-8035.0-8065.30" target="_blank">still facilitated over-the-counter</a>, meaning lenders and borrowers have no way of accessing live price data. Only the brokers and “TBTF” banks have access to this information, and this allows them to charge  practically whatever they want without anybody  knowing if they received a fair market price. </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"textColor":"vivid-red","customFontSize":40,"className":"cursive-background-image-2"} -->
<p style="font-size:40px" class="has-text-color has-vivid-red-color cursive-background-image-2"><em>…<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>I think the securities lending market is just like the mob. I think it’s completely rigged</strong></span>. It’s a completely manipulated black hole<strong>...</strong><br><br>--Marc Cohodes, Copper River Partners</em></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Experts have described this system as <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://archive.is/0KSRT#selection-1005.281-1005.307" target="_blank">the mother of all dark pools</a>, and people have been calling for change for practically <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20070106082943/http://www.vodiagroup.com/pdfs/FourMyths.pdf" target="_blank">two decades</a> now. <br><br>Pictured below is an example of how this process works.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":31579,"width":893,"height":484,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-29-11-32-15-702.jpg?fit=1024%2C556&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31579" width="893" height="484"/></figure></div>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":30,"className":"cursive-background-image-3"} -->
<p style="font-size:30px" class="cursive-background-image-3"><em>"The current stock loan market involves <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">high search costs</span></strong> <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">and inefficient pricing</span></strong>.</em><br><br><em>It can take <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">numerous phone calls over several hours to locate a hot stock and negotiate pricing</span></strong>. The lender has no indicative level of pricing other than the demand information provided by the brokers, which the lender has no way to verify. In other words, the securities lending market requires considerable manual effort to complete transactions that <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>in other markets take seconds or minutes at most</strong></span>. Because of the fragmented nature of the market, <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">identical loans can trade simultaneously through different channels at very different prices</span></strong>. These high search costs preclude arbitrage across liquidity pools"</em><br><br><a href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-24833.5-24875.41" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-24833.5-24875.41</a></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"blue-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="blue-yellow-background-link"><a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Quadriserv/AQS, SL-x (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-1763.0-1823.89" target="_blank">Quadriserv/AQS, SL-x</a>, and <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Data Explorers (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-1763.0-1823.89" target="_blank">Data Explorers</a> all spent several years creating an <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-1903.0-1955.93" target="_blank">electronic exchange</a> for this massive $1.75 trillion market, and  their technology could have finally put an end to this <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-1229.0-1259.90" target="_blank">backward and opaque</a> system that has been plaguing pensioners, endowments, and hedge funds for more than <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20070106082943/http://www.vodiagroup.com/pdfs/FourMyths.pdf" target="_blank">20 years</a>.  Unfortunately, even though their technology took decades of collaboration and <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="$100's of millions (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-21667.20-21667.87" target="_blank">$100's of millions</a> in start-up capital, they were all blocked by these mega-banks. </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:olympus-google-fonts/google-fonts {"blockType":"h1","fontID":"helvetica","fontSize":49,"align":"center","content":"It threatened their cartel"} /-->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"red-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="red-yellow-background-link">The mega-banks that dominate this industry simply had too much to lose by allowing us to have access to this information, so in order to stop this technology from reaching the market, they <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="banded together (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-9859.0-9867.11" target="_blank">banded together</a> and <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="refused to provide key services (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-17613.0-17625.85" target="_blank">refused to provide key services</a> to these bright start ups, even going so far as to <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="threaten their top hedge fund clients (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-2785.1-2809.89" target="_blank">threaten their top hedge fund clients</a> with the loss of critical prime brokerage services if they found out they were using their platforms.  <br><br>This is why still to this day in the year 2020, with AI tech; quantum computing; social media; smart phones; automated vehicles; and all the other amazing technologies that have completely changed our world, there is still no centralized exchange, and no electronic platform for stock loans. <br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>In 2016, it was estimated that these brokers were extracting<a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" 65% of the revenues (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-24495.33-24495.57" target="_blank"> 65% of the revenues</a> from the stock loan market; most of which was going to a very small group of <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="investment banks (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-8349.5-8379.82" target="_blank">investment banks</a>.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Over time, the cumulative effect this can have on our pension funds is astronomical. Just to put that into perspective, <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://archive.is/hWtnX#selection-153.0-167.68" target="_blank">Frontline estimated</a> that as little as a 2% annual fee charged by your average mutual fund over a period of 50 years would result in a 66% reduction to your retirement savings.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"red-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="red-yellow-background-link">What’s worse is that they seem to think this is some kind of joke, referring to the collusive private gatherings that they use as a conduit to <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="dredge up schemes (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-15557.2-15593.13" target="_blank">dredge up schemes</a> to maintain their dominance over this essential financial service as a meeting of the "<a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Five Families (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-15471.0-15489.88" target="_blank">Five Families</a> "; and hence we are simply forced to hand over large chunks of our retirement savings to this small group of <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="investments banks (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-8349.5-8379.82" target="_blank">investments banks</a> like it's some <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="protection racket run by the mafia (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-10317.4-10355.1" target="_blank">protection racket run by the mafia</a>.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"blue-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="blue-yellow-background-link">On an annualized basis, the stock loan industry is estimated to produce <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="$9 billion in revenue (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-1731.1-1743.19" target="_blank">$9 billion in revenue</a>.  That equates to $180 billion in profits over a period of 20 years, and this is without accounting for compounding interest. <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-10419.0-10455.89" target="_blank">Quadriserv</a> -- one of the companies that attempted to challenge these brokers stranglehold over the industry -- estimated that their platform would have saved pensioners <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="$4.5 billion per year (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-26655.0-26691.78" target="_blank">$4.5 billion per year</a>, and in the words of one high level bank executive, it could “do the work of <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="6 traders in 1 (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-21705.31-21705.81" target="_blank">6 traders in 1</a>".</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:olympus-google-fonts/google-fonts {"blockType":"h1","fontID":"helvetica","fontSize":49,"align":"center","content":"The New York Clearing Cartel"} /-->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>As we all know, history has a tendency to repeat itself, and this <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Quadriserv/AQS, SL-x, and Data Explorers (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-1763.0-1823.89" target="_blank">Quadriserv/AQS, SL-x, and Data Explorers</a> situation is definitely not the first time something like this has happened. It perfectly emulates the Cartel from the days of the New York Association when a consortium of the country’s largest financial institutions could shutdown any bank in the nation simply by refusing their services.  In fact, it was this very behavior that eventually went on to become the primary focal point of the <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Pujo Committee (opens in a new tab)" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pujo_Committee" target="_blank">Pujo Committee</a> in 1913, immediately before the passing of the Federal Reserve Act.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Included below are key excepts from that Committee which will show you the true power of a clearinghouse.   Key quotes from the book, "Other People's Money and How the Bankers Use It"(1914), will also be included, and everything has been broken down so it will only take about <em>5 minutes</em> to read.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:olympus-google-fonts/google-fonts {"blockType":"h1","fontID":"helvetica","fontSize":50,"align":"center","content":"From the Depository Trust and Clearing Corporation's 2018 Annual Report"} /-->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31157,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2019-09-04-11-59-04-872.jpg?fit=1024%2C487&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31157"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31159,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2019-09-04-11-59-55-398.jpg?fit=1024%2C487&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31159"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31160,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2019-09-04-12-00-10-763.jpg?fit=1024%2C487&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31160"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":39,"className":"cursive-background-image-3"} -->
<p style="font-size:39px" class="cursive-background-image-3">(<strong>February 28, 1913</strong>) "<em>Report of the Committee appointed pursuant to House resolutions 429 and 504 to investigate the concentration of control of money and credit".</em></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31198,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-27-21-55-03-171.jpg?fit=1024%2C365&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31198"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":40,"className":"back-ground-colour-1"} -->
<p style="font-size:40px" class="back-ground-colour-1">Knickerboker Trust was banned from using the clearing services of National Bank of Commerce of New York, leading to its immediate collapse.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31201,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-27-23-24-10-576.jpg?fit=1024%2C341&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31201"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":41,"className":"back-ground-colour-1"} -->
<p style="font-size:41px" class="back-ground-colour-1">Without the services of the the New York Association, the most dominant Clearing House at the time, it was well known by customers and bank owners alike that they would almost certainly fail within as little as a few days.  </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31203,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-27-23-26-03-761.jpg?fit=1024%2C457&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31203"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31205,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-27-23-29-42-696.jpg?fit=1024%2C286&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31205"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":41,"className":"back-ground-colour-1"} -->
<p style="font-size:41px" class="back-ground-colour-1">Even so much as a rumor would cause a bank run</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31207,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-27-23-31-01-555.jpg?fit=1024%2C359&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31207"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":41,"className":"back-ground-colour-1"} -->
<p style="font-size:41px" class="back-ground-colour-1">The New York Clearing House forces Oriental Bank to stop working with two Brooklyn Banks, even though they pose no risk to anybody and represent an important percentage of Oriental Bank's  profits</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31209,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-27-23-34-29-393.jpg?fit=1024%2C573&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31209"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31211,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-27-23-36-51-816.jpg?fit=1024%2C253&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31211"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31213,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-27-23-41-45-035.jpg?fit=1024%2C441&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31213"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":32754,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-02-01-07-13-495.jpg?fit=1024%2C410&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-32754"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":35997,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-14-18-12-58-902.jpg?fit=1024%2C486&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-35997"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":29,"className":"cursive-background-image-2"} -->
<p style="font-size:29px" class="cursive-background-image-2"><em>"The men who through their control over the funds of our railroads and industrial companies are able to direct where such funds shall be kept and thus to create these great reservoirs of the people's money, are the ones who are in position to tap those reservoirs for the ventures in which they are interested<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> and to prevent their being tapped for purposes of which they do not approve</span></strong>. The latter is quite as important a factor as the former. <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">It is the controlling consideration in its effect on competition</span></strong> in the railroad and industrial world." <br></em><br><br>--(1914) Other People’s Money and How the Bankers Use It<br><a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" https://archive.is/FjfOR#selection-2791.0-2794.0 (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/FjfOR#selection-2791.0-2794.0" target="_blank"> https://archive.is/FjfOR#selection-2791.0-2794.0</a></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31223,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-28-00-12-04-810.jpg?fit=1024%2C182&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31223"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31225,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-28-00-15-24-271.jpg?fit=1024%2C353&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31225"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":41,"className":"back-ground-colour-1"} -->
<p style="font-size:41px" class="back-ground-colour-1">A sort of gentleman's agreement decided the fate of the entire country..</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31226,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-28-00-17-09-160.jpg?fit=1024%2C353&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31226"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":29,"className":"cursive-background-image-2"} -->
<p style="font-size:29px" class="cursive-background-image-2"><em>“These bankers are, of course, able men possessed of large fortunes; but the most potent factor in their control of business is not the possession of extraordinary ability or huge wealth.<strong>&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;">The key to their power is Combination</span></strong>….<br><br>“<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">There is the obvious consolidation of banks and trust companies</span></strong>; the less obvious affiliations–through stockholdings, voting trusts and interlocking directorates–of banking institutions&nbsp;<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">which are not legally connected</span></strong>; and the joint transactions,&nbsp;<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">gentlemen’s agreements, and “banking ethics</span>”&nbsp;</strong>which eliminate competition among the investment bankers”.</em><br><br>--“Other People’s Money and How the Bankers Use It”, (1914)<br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":41,"className":"back-ground-colour-1"} -->
<p style="font-size:41px" class="back-ground-colour-1">All it took was 1/4 of its members to block somebody from joining,  regardless of their qualifications, and even if these people were competing with the appellant.  </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31233,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-28-00-43-54-270.jpg?fit=1024%2C337&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31233"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31234,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-28-00-43-26-632.jpg?fit=1024%2C428&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31234"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31236,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-28-00-45-25-287.jpg?fit=1024%2C259&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31236"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31238,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-28-00-48-24-366.jpg?fit=1024%2C375&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31238"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":41,"className":"back-ground-colour-1"} -->
<p style="font-size:41px" class="back-ground-colour-1">Even if the bank was a member of the club, in the event of a change of control, the bank would be expelled if the members did not approve of the new management.  <br><br>It's a clique; a private club; a Cartel.  </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31241,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-28-00-49-50-757.jpg?fit=1024%2C212&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31241"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31243,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-28-00-56-28-548.jpg?fit=1024%2C245&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-31243"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Do you see how powerful these organizations are? They shutdown two healthy banks for no reason whatsoever. People's life savings were in those banks, and this was before social security, so you could literally starve back then; you and your family.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"red-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="red-yellow-background-link">What most people might not recognize is that profits are only secondary to these people.  Sure, you can never go wrong with profits, but it goes <em>much </em>deeper than that, and the reason why the <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-14455.5-14497.19" target="_blank">blood drained out of that bankers face</a> at the mere mention of Quadriserv's technology has very little do with profits.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>If the stock loan market were to emerge from the shadows of the "OTC" and on to a public exchange where everything is closely scrutinized, it would be much easier to track who was borrowing stock, and at what price, which could potentially reveal what these mega-banks are up to behind the scenes. People might even start recommending that they include all these loans into a Consolidated Tape, making it much harder for them to hide their activities.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":40,"className":"cursive-background-image-2"} -->
<p style="font-size:40px" class="cursive-background-image-2"><em>"Under Graber, <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>I learned that Wall Street was an illusion</strong></span>,”.. “There were different magicians using different tricks in different ways. But <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>everyone cheated.</strong> </span>It shocked me so much in the beginning. I admired these people. And they cheated",</em> <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://archive.is/kvr0n#selection-1871.0-1874.0" target="_blank">Samuel Israel III</a></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":40,"className":"cursive-background-image"} -->
<p style="font-size:40px" class="cursive-background-image"><br><br><br><br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Keeping this market in the dark doesn't just give you control over the spread, like what is seen here.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":31579,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img src="https://interactiveswingtrades.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-29-11-32-15-702-1024x556.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-31579"/></figure></div>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"red-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="red-yellow-background-link">It also gives you control over the supply of equities, and it even allows you manipulate voting outcomes in contested elections.<br><br><br><br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"red-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="red-yellow-background-link"><br> <br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"textColor":"vivid-red","customFontSize":39,"className":"cursive-background-image-2"} -->
<p style="font-size:39px" class="has-text-color has-vivid-red-color cursive-background-image-2"><em><span style="color:#cf2e2e" class="tadv-color">“And then as time went on and/or a position got bigger, the rate would get jacked up on us...... So our cost of doing business in a particular name would<strong> </strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>go from not costing us anything to costing us tens of millions of dollars"</strong></span>… </span><br></em><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"blue-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="blue-yellow-background-link"><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>This <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="exact same scenario (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/c0Qt6#selection-29315.0-29318.0" target="_blank">exact same scenario</a> occurred before the financial crisis when CDO's were still popular. The banks refused to let anybody have access to live pricing data, so everything had to be traded on the OTC markets with no central clearing.  Even when they were offered the opportunity to trade on a public exchange, <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://archive.is/D2BWU#selection-961.0-965.270" target="_blank">they still refused</a>.<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":40,"className":"cursive-background-image"} -->
<p style="font-size:40px" class="cursive-background-image"><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"red-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="red-yellow-background-link"><br><br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":52,"className":"cursive-background-image"} -->
<p style="font-size:52px" class="cursive-background-image"><br><br><br><em>Give me control over nations equity supply and I care not who makes its laws</em>..<br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":38214,"width":924,"height":470,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Oceania_Map.svg_-2.png?fit=1024%2C521&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-38214" width="924" height="470"/></figure></div>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><br><br><br><br><br><br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>If somebody were to tell you that you do not technically own your shares in a public company, would you believe them? Probably not, right? That seems rather ridiculous, doesn't it?  Many people have their life-savings invested in the stock market, and how could somebody else own something that you paid for with your own money?  <br><br>Unfortunately it's true, and you are not the legal owner of your investments. It is actually the banks and brokers that are the true legal owners, and you are just issued an entitlement; an unusual relationship that they characterize as "<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://archive.is/T1d0Y#selection-1291.0-1294.0" target="_blank">street name</a>" ownership, and all shares are held in book-entry form (electronically) at the DTCC, with the banks and brokers acting as the <em>registered holders</em> on the company's books.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":32048,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://archive.is/GsfAh" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-30-14-53-30-524.jpg?fit=1024%2C274&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-32048"/></a><figcaption>https://www.sec.gov/comments/4-725/4725-5335206-184008.pdf</figcaption></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><br><br>By transferring ownership to the DTCC and registering the brokers as the true holders of your stocks, it solved the problem of constantly having to transfer physical certificates from one location to another; a process that was cumbersome and created liability issues. <br><br>Back the in the 70's they describe this unusual relationship as a “Jumbo Certificate”<br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":32768,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><a href="https://ia801700.us.archive.org/23/items/fsec00unit/fsec00unit.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-01-31-22-44-56-632.jpg?fit=1024%2C639&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-32768"/></a></figure></div>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><br><br>A perfect example of this ownership structure is illustrated in the document snapshot pictured below from a recent Broadridge Financial Services note offering, dated Dec.5th, 2019, only a few months ago.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"blue-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="blue-yellow-background-link">They refer to this debt obligation  as a "<em>Global Note</em> " that is owned by the DTC (a DTCC subsidiary).<br><br>It also says that the owners of the "beneficial interests" will not be <em>legally </em>considered owners of "<em>any notes</em> " under the "Global Note".  A <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="&quot;beneficial interest&quot; (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/T1d0Y#selection-1291.270-1291.344" target="_blank">"beneficial interest"</a> would be you, as you are the brokers' customer for which they have granted you "<em>entitlements</em> " to these investments.<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":37,"className":"cursive-background-image"} -->
<p style="font-size:37px" class="cursive-background-image"><em>"Under Article 8, the beneficial owner of the shares held in a custodial account with an intermediary (such as a broker) is </em><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>considered to be the holder of a “securities entitlement” in a “financial asset” </em></span></strong><em>which is ultimately held by a depository",  </em><br><br>--<em>Marcel Kahan, The Georgetown Law Journal<br></em><br><br><br><br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":32970,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/d12Pk6.yWgd.htm?Find=%22Ownership%20of%20Beneficial%20Interests%22&amp;Line=1480#Line1480" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-02-17-44-54-990.jpg?fit=1024%2C649&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-32970"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"blue-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="blue-yellow-background-link">They say explicitly in the first paragraph  that the DTC will credit the "beneficial interests " represented by the "global note " to the accounts of the "<em>participants</em>".  <br><br>But who are these <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="participants (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.lawinsider.com/dictionary/dtc-participant" target="_blank">participants</a>?</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":31153,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://archive.is/OGRnf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://interactiveswingtrades.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-27-17-00-32-252-1024x466.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-31153"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The "participants" are the same banks and brokers that are buying the debt securities from Broadridge.  <br><br>But doesn't that make them the <em>indirect  </em>owners of this "<em>Jumbo Certificate</em> " -- or in this case, "Global Note " -- through their ownership of the DTCC?  <br><br><br><br>The answer is yes, it does.<br><br><br><br><br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><br><br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>In the age of artificial intelligence, crypto currencies, smart phones and quantum computing, you might be wondering why we still need these brokers and banks to act as the legal owners of our investments. Nobody uses paper certificates anymore, and certainly there should be some kind of SAAS technology out there by now that could solve the liability and book-keeping issues that come with transferring these ownership interests back and forth between accounts.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>In reality, this system hasn't been necessary for practically for <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20070106082943/http://www.vodiagroup.com/pdfs/FourMyths.pdf" target="_blank">20 years</a>, and many <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://scholarship.law.upenn.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1163&amp;context=faculty_scholarship" target="_blank">experts </a> are equally as perplexed by this unusual "<em>entitlement</em> " system as they are about the opaque black-hole that governs the stock loan industry today, where retiree's (the elderly) are literally being forced to utilize middlemen that actively collude to separate buyers and sellers so they can charge higher spreads.<br><br>They don't even let companies send "proxy" (voter) materials directly to their shareholders; the company is forced to send the voting materials to the brokers first, and only then will they send them to you.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":32051,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://archive.is/GsfAh" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-30-15-04-13-607.jpg?fit=1024%2C373&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-32051"/></a><figcaption>https://www.sec.gov/comments/4-725/4725-5335206-184008.pdf</figcaption></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":32053,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://archive.is/GsfAh" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-30-15-05-41-506.jpg?fit=1024%2C391&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-32053"/></a><figcaption>https://www.sec.gov/comments/4-725/4725-5335206-184008.pdf</figcaption></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Pictured below is an illustration of how this process works.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":32788,"width":948,"height":1035,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><a href="https://ia801700.us.archive.org/23/items/fsec00unit/fsec00unit.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://interactiveswingtrades.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-01-31-23-59-46-385.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-32788" width="948" height="1035"/></a><figcaption>https://ia801700.us.archive.org/23/items/fsec00unit/fsec00unit.pdf</figcaption></figure></div>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>If you had trouble with that first one, this next illustration might be easier to understand.  That other one is kind of old -- from 1976 to be exact. <br><br>Yes, the same system that existed back then is still being used today. </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":33133,"width":891,"height":476,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-02-22-13-11-908.jpg?fit=1024%2C548&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-33133" width="891" height="476"/></figure></div>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":33134,"width":1141,"height":520,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-02-22-11-30-248.jpg?fit=1024%2C467&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-33134" width="1141" height="520"/></figure></div>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Guess who these brokers contract out to send you these "proxy" materials (voting cards).</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":33055,"width":951,"height":434,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-01-31-15-49-10-081.jpg?fit=1024%2C468&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-33055" width="951" height="434"/></figure></div>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":30} -->
<p style="font-size:30px">Broadridge Financial Services..</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":32993,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-02-16-40-48-183.jpg?fit=1024%2C354&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-32993"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":32995,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><a href="https://archive.is/suOUC" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://interactiveswingtrades.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-02-18-34-43-100.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-32995"/></a><figcaption><a href="https://east.proxyvote.com/pv/web?pvskey=br">https://east.proxyvote.com/pv/web?pvskey=br</a></figcaption></figure></div>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>They control 80% of the "proxy" (voter) communication industry.  Don't worry, we're just getting started.   It gets much worse.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":33375,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/d1a6sv.h2.htm?Find=industry&amp;Line=435#Line435" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-03-19-48-08-083.jpg?fit=1024%2C364&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-33375"/></a><figcaption>https://www.secinfo.com/d1a6sv.h2.htm?Find=industry&amp;Line=435#Line435</figcaption></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Did you know that  you can borrow shares immediately before a corporate election for the sole purpose of influencing the outcome?  Yes, in America if you borrow shares, the voting rights are transferred to you.  </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":32099,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20121113172601/http://www.rwbaird.com/bolimages/Media/PDF/FI/Your-Financial-Goals/Margin-Risk-Disclosure.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-30-16-56-06-960.jpg?fit=1024%2C373&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-32099"/></a><figcaption><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20121113172601/http://www.rwbaird.com/bolimages/Media/PDF/FI/Your-Financial-Goals/Margin-Risk-Disclosure.pdf">https://web.archive.org/web/20121113172601/http://www.rwbaird.com/bolimages/Media/PDF/FI/Your-Financial-Goals/Margin-Risk-Disclosure.pdf</a></figcaption></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>You get to keep the dividend, but not the vote?  That seems rather counter intuitive, doesn't it?  Or better yet, ripe for exploitation?  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br>..That's because it is..<br><br><br><br><br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":35,"className":"cursive-background-image-2"} -->
<p style="font-size:35px" class="cursive-background-image-2">"<em>The existing system of shareholder voting is crude, imprecise, and fragile. Gil Sparks, a leading Delaware lawyer, estimates that, <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">in a contest that is closer than 55 to 45%, </span></strong></em><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>there is no verifiable answer to the question “who won?”</em></span></strong> <em>"</em><br><br>--<a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="The Hanging Chads of Corporate Voting (opens in a new tab)" href="https://scholarship.law.upenn.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1163&amp;context=faculty_scholarship" target="_blank">The Hanging Chads of Corporate Voting</a><br><br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":32055,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2020-01-30-15-09-20-593.jpg?fit=1024%2C433&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-32055"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Over and over again,  for years on end, it has been show that votes are constantly being misappropriated, yet the only entity that can reconcile this problem is owned and controlled by them: The Depository Trust and Clearing Corporation.  <br><br>Broadridge, the company they contract out to send us our proxy (voting) materials, even admits in their corporate filings that their relationship with these brokers constitutes as a "<em>conflict of interest</em> ".<br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":32972,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/d12Pk6.yWgd.htm?Find=Underwriting&amp;Line=1750#Line1750" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-02-16-46-37-581.jpg?fit=1024%2C572&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-32972"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"red-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="red-yellow-background-link">Should we really trust these people to fairly tabulate our votes? You can make $100's of million's from being on the right side of a corporate merger, and as recent history has shown, <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://interactiveswingtrades.com/scandals/" target="_blank">these banks will rig anything</a> so long as they can get away with it.  Only <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://archive.is/D88Y4#selection-399.51-403.107" target="_blank">30% of shareholders</a> were shown to have voted in 2014, so it's not like it would be hard for them to figure out a way to rig this too.<br> <br>That alone should be enough to cause you concern, but combined with the fact that they can borrow shares for the sole purpose of influencing an election, and its easy to see how this system can be manipulated.  They even have a name for this practice:  <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Vote Buying (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/JQZh6#selection-34.1-14853.20" target="_blank">Vote Buying</a>. <br><br> Yes, <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Vote Buying (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/JQZh6#selection-15527.1-15545.34" target="_blank">Vote Buying</a>..</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><br>From now on we're going to try to avoid using the word "Proxy" because it acts to cloak what is actually going on here: a vote, not a "proxy". That word makes it sound much more complicated than it actually is, especially considering all the technology we have today.  Every country in the Western World holds elections, yet for some strange reason, the only place that exhibits such unusual complications is on the stock market; the lifeblood of the American economy.<br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"blue-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="blue-yellow-background-link">Bob Drummond wrote an <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="article  (opens in a new tab)" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20060421085925/http://www.rgm.com/articles/FalseProxies.pdf" target="_blank">article </a>about this for Bloomberg years ago, but in typical Bloomberg fashion, <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="it was deleted (opens in a new tab)" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20060421085925/http://www.rgm.com/articles/FalseProxies.pdf" target="_blank">it was deleted</a>).  </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:olympus-google-fonts/google-fonts {"blockType":"h1","fontID":"helvetica","content":"From: \u0022Double Voting in Proxy Contests Threatens Shareholder Democracy\u0022, Bloomberg, By Bob Drummond"} /-->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":29,"className":"cursive-background-image-3"} -->
<p style="font-size:29px" class="cursive-background-image-3">"<em>It is an abomination</em>,'' says Thomas Montrone, chief executive officer of Cranford, New Jersey-based Registrar &amp; Transfer Co., which oversees shareholder elections. "A lot of the time we have no idea who's entitled to vote and who isn't. It's nothing short of criminal.''<br><br>"In a little-known quirk of Wall Street bookkeeping, with the growth of short sales, which involve the resale of borrowed securities, stocks can be lent repeatedly". <br><a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/PR9Ww#selection-3583.0-3586.0" target="_blank">https://archive.is/PR9Ww#selection-3583.0-3586.0</a></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":33,"className":"cursive-background-image-3"} -->
<p style="font-size:33px" class="cursive-background-image-3"><em>...."The <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">loans allow three or four owners to cast votes</span></strong> based on holdings of the same shares".</em><br><a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/PR9Ww#selection-3587.0-3590.0" target="_blank">https://archive.is/PR9Ww#selection-3587.0-3590.0</a></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":35698,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2019-12-07-23-14-50-580.jpg?fit=1024%2C411&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-35698"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"red-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="red-yellow-background-link">Drummond later described three specific contested elections where this was known to have occurred.   As you can see in the image below, all one needs is a few extra shares to tip the pendulum in a contested election, making  the corporate executives and <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="wolf -packs (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/CfilN#selection-2889.0-2908.0" target="_blank">wolf -packs</a> who front-run these predatory schemes millions from carefully facilitated mergers, acquisitions and hostile take overs. </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":32108,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bandicam-2019-12-07-20-56-46-734-1-1.jpg?fit=1024%2C419&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-32108"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":30,"className":"cursive-background-image"} -->
<p style="font-size:30px" class="cursive-background-image">(CARL T. HAGBERG AND ASSOCIATES)  "Over-voting is, quite simply, untenable. Allowing it to continue makes a mockery of the idea of corporate democracy. There is ample evidence that people do try to “game” the system, since votes do indeed have value - especially when the<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em> voting outcomes have the potential to move the stock price</em></span></strong>, as often they demonstrably do. (See, for example, <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" href="https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=686026&amp;download=yes" target="_blank">“Vote Trading and Information Aggregation”</a></span></strong> which is easily accessible on the Internet and which documents <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>huge spikes in share purchases near meeting record dates and corresponding sales immediately thereafter</em></span></strong>). There is also a great deal of evidence that the “gamesters” quite often succeed in gaming the vote, since, (a) as the study pointed out, <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>one can buy votes for about $6 per million votes and </em></span></strong>(b) vote buyers will vote 100% of the time, while long-term owners tend not to vote at all, which allows the voters with “duplicate voting credentials” not just to go undetected, but to have their way in terms of the election outcomes. It is especially important to note in the context of election “gaming” that the interests of short-term and long-term owners are, almost always, diametrically opposed in election contests".  <br><a href="https://archive.is/aUv1B" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">https://archive.is/aUv1B</a><br><a href="http://www.sec.gov/comments/s7-14-10/s71410-68.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="http://www.sec.gov/comments/s7-14-10/s71410-68.pdf (opens in a new tab)">http://www.sec.gov/comments/s7-14-10/s71410-68.pdf</a></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":33,"className":"cursive-background-image-3"} -->
<p style="font-size:33px" class="cursive-background-image-3">"The customer doesn't know this is happening,'' says John Wilcox, head of corporate governance at TIAA-CREF, the biggest private U.S. pension plan for teachers.  Often, the broker still permits the customer to vote the shares even though they're out on loan. That policy is not sound. It definitely means that shares can be voted twice.''<br><a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/PR9Ww#selection-4015.0-4018.0" target="_blank">https://archive.is/PR9Ww#selection-4015.0-4018.0</a></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>But most of the time none of these tactics are necessary, because again, most people usually don't even show up to vote anyway.  </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":40,"className":"cursive-background-image"} -->
<p style="font-size:40px" class="cursive-background-image"><em>"It's invisible,'' says Paul Schulman, executive managing director of Altman Group Inc., a proxy solicitor based in Lyndhurst, New Jersey. Most of the time you don't get overvotes because so many shareholders don't vote.''</em></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>They've certainly shown that they are perfectly capable of <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="rigging everything else (opens in a new tab)" href="https://interactiveswingtrades.com/scandals/" target="_blank">rigging everything else</a>.   These people will do anything for a buck; they will even coerce the directors of the DTCC into blocking new technology, costing pensioners hundreds of billions of dollars.<br><br>Pensioners: those people who <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="worked their whole lives (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.pewresearch.org/fact-tank/2018/08/07/for-most-us-workers-real-wages-have-barely-budged-for-decades/" target="_blank">worked their whole lives</a> and finally want to settle down after decades of toiling at their job 5, maybe even 6 days a week. They took you to school, fed you while you were a child; taught you everything you know about life..</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

