<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":33340,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-03-18-07-54-456.jpg?fit=1024%2C521&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-33340"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>What does this all mean?<br><br>Who knows..<br><br>They've been at this for more than a decade now, so it just seems rather odd that you can't even visit the website of what appears to be one of the most prominent advocacy groups fighting for change on this matter without risking your computer being infected with a virus.  </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":33709,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://archive.is/h7XEs" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-04-14-57-34-053.jpg?fit=1024%2C653&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-33709"/></a><figcaption><a href="https://archive.is/h7XEs">https://archive.is/h7XEs</a></figcaption></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":33710,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-04-14-55-29-683.jpg?fit=1024%2C612&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-33710"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":33794,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://archive.is/prjyQ" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-04-18-16-05-356.jpg?fit=1024%2C407&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-33794"/></a><figcaption><a href="https://archive.is/prjyQ">https://archive.is/prjyQ</a></figcaption></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Does corporate election meddling happen all the time?<br><br>Probably not.  <br><br>Can it happen?  Yes, it's been shown to happen on numerous occasions, and  extensive research has been published on this fact.  <br><br>The ability to just issue stock loans to investors in the dark and devoid of any public scrutiny is obviously something that creates a multitude of opportunities for misuse; especially when you can fail to deliver -- issue fictitious <em>entitlements </em>-- which we are about touch on next.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":34,"className":"cursive-background-image"} -->
<p style="font-size:34px" class="cursive-background-image">"<em>As a result of these NYSE administrative proceedings, the securities industry adopted written guidelines to address this reconciliation problem.<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">These guidelines permit brokers to select one of two reconciliation methods</span></strong></em>"</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"cursive-background-image-2"} -->
<p class="cursive-background-image-2"><em>The securities industry guidelines that provide two methods of beneficial owner reconciliation <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">should be replaced with an SEC rule that requires pre-mailing reconciliation (finding out which Shares Entitlements Are Fake and which ones are real  before letting everybody vote, obviously) as the only method for brokers and other intermediaries.</span></strong></em><br><br><em>Street name positions should be reconciled as of the record date (the record date is the last day you are allowed to vote) for each shareholder meeting, <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">in order to avoid discrepancies in tabulating final vote counts and to avoid distributing proxy materials to beneficial owners who are ineligible to vote</span></strong> (Fake Shares).</em></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":33164,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-01-17-46-28-681.jpg?fit=1024%2C482&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-33164"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":33165,"width":916,"height":431,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-01-17-46-24-010.jpg?fit=1024%2C482&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-33165" width="916" height="431"/></figure></div>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"red-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="red-yellow-background-link">You see, money is just the icing on the cake for these people. As they say, it comes, and it goes. What is much more important is maintaining control over <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="key infrastructure (opens in a new tab)" href="https://prospect.org/power/jpmorgan-gets-back-into-the-electricity-business/" target="_blank">key infrastructure</a>, giving you the power to swing the pendulum in your favor when the opportunity presents itself.<br><br>If you have the ability to facilitate a merger through your control of the voting mechanism, not only can you  make money for yourself, but you can also facilitate transactions for your preferred customers; whether that be a manager of one of these corporations, or a hedge fund client. </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"blue-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="blue-yellow-background-link">This also applies to pricing, where through failure to delivers, these banks and brokers can artificially control supply and demand by selling entitlements to investors that <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20070106083509/http://www.vodiagroup.com/pdfs/seclending1.pdf" target="_blank">don't actually exist</a>.  <br><br>This can become problematic because it gives you the ability to sell large volumes of stock at <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20200220024337/https://interactiveswingtrades.com/2019/12/23/hmny/" target="_blank">artificially inflated price levels</a>, which can incentivize  market manipulation schemes that involve coordinated groups of people pumping up the share price so they can sell IOU's to unsuspecting investors at prices where there <em>aught not to be any shares available for sale</em> <em>in the first place</em>; something that was recently shown to have occurred when a market maker was caught <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="selling fake shares (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/Mo0Xh#selection-1619.0-1669.13" target="_blank">selling fake shares</a> in a variety micro-caps using his <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="market maker exception (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.sec.gov/investor/pubs/regsho.htm" target="_blank">market maker exception</a>.<br><br>TLRY is a great example of a situation where this could be abused.  The market is supposed to regulate itself through supply and demand, but if you can just <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20200220024337/https://interactiveswingtrades.com/2019/12/23/hmny/" target="_blank">fabricate a parabolic move</a>, then sell shares when there shouldn't be any shares available in the first place, you've essentially just sold people stock at a <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="fictitious price (opens in a new tab)" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20200220024337/https://interactiveswingtrades.com/2019/12/23/hmny/" target="_blank">fictitious price</a> that otherwise would not have existed under normal market conditions.   <br><br>Should we be surprised?  Technically a stock broker is just a retailer, and what do retailers usually do best? Trick you into buying things that you don't actually need at inflated prices.<br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":28,"className":"cursive-background-image-3"} -->
<p style="font-size:28px" class="cursive-background-image-3"><em>“Trade settlement is what converts market liquidity into actual cash liquidity for firms and capital markets... “You wouldn’t buy a house and show up on closing day, take title, rent out the house and collect the rent, all before paying. Yet <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>that’s what’s happening every day in the financial system.</strong></span>”....</em><br><em><br>--Fred Sommers, <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Basis Point Group (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/DPfqw#selection-1751.0-1754.0" target="_blank">Basis Point Group</a></em></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"red-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="red-yellow-background-link"><br><br>Other problems could arise when people start lending out these IOU's, which is technically just a <em><a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/k3NL2" target="_blank">fictitious loan</a></em>; one of the most egregious forms of financial frauds one can imagine.  That would be like loaning someone fake gold 100 years ago, then charging them interest under the threat that if they didn't pay you back, you would come seize their assets.  </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"blue-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="blue-yellow-background-link"><br><br>Extensive research has been published on <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://archive.org/details/MaxKeiserRadio-TheTruthAboutMarkets-15May2010" target="_blank">this topic</a> by many  <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="victims of this fraudulent activity (opens in a new tab)" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20110902145244/https://www.deepcapture.com/wp-content/uploads/story-of-dendreon.pdf" target="_blank">victims of this fraudulent activity</a>, with academics, politicians and even regulators chiming in on this <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20110902145244/https://www.deepcapture.com/wp-content/uploads/story-of-dendreon.pdf" target="_blank">strange phenomena</a>, but most of the time it just gets <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="lost in the echo chamber (opens in a new tab)" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20160505014449/http://antisocialmedia.net/media/2007.10.09%20(J%20Welborn)%20Married%20Puts%20and%20Reverse%20Conversions.pdf" target="_blank">lost in the echo chamber</a>, forever buried down the memory hole.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":36560,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:jYvAhSGGL8cJ:https://www.sec.gov/rules/concept/2010/34-62495.pdf+&amp;cd=1&amp;hl=en&amp;ct=clnk&amp;gl=ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Even-though-the-broker-dealer-has-not-received-the-securities-they-will-credit-its-customers’-accounts-with-the-purchased-securities.jpg?fit=1024%2C577&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-36560"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"red-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="red-yellow-background-link"><br>Issuing multiples rights to investors on the same securities -- you don't think they'd do it? They've done it before; they do it with everything, so why not equities? <br><br>There is so many different options on the same stock that it would probably make your head spin; so many different bonds on the same company; bonds of bonds; GSE's and ETF's representing the same group of companies and sectors; bet's on bets; and exotic derivatives piled on top of derivatives -- so what makes you think they won't sell you more entitlements to shares than actually exist? <br><br>They already entitle their clients to <em>fictitious </em>votes, and it's not like it would be hard. Remember, they own the clearinghouse, and enjoy a virtual monopoly over the stock market, with 39% of deposits concentrated into only 4 banks, and <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://interactiveswingtrades.com/2019/11/18/flash-fact-six-brokers-control-roughly-70-of-the-prime-brokerage-industry-hfalert-com/" target="_blank">50% of the prime brokerage industry</a> controlled by only three companies. Considering everything else they've been caught doing in the past, the real question we should all be asking ourselves is why <em>wouldn't </em>they do something this? They don't even care about their own clients, referring to them as <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://archive.is/kioML#selection-1387.1-1402.0" target="_blank">"Muppet's"</a><br><br>They rigged the <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="municipal bond market (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.rollingstone.com/politics/politics-news/the-scam-wall-street-learned-from-the-mafia-190232/" target="_blank">municipal bond market</a>, they rigged the <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="treasury bond markets (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.nytimes.com/1991/08/10/business/salomon-brothers-admits-violations-at-treasury-sales.html" target="_blank">treasury bond markets</a>; they rigged the <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="foreign exchange market (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2015/05/21/business/dealbook/5-big-banks-to-pay-billions-and-plead-guilty-in-currency-and-interest-rate-cases.html?_r=0" target="_blank">foreign exchange market</a>; they <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="rigged the metals market (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.silverdoctors.com/gold/gold-news/ted-butler-the-genius-of-jp-morgan-the-profit-generating-machine/" target="_blank">rigged the metals market</a>; they <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="rigged the energy market (opens in a new tab)" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enron" target="_blank">rigged the energy market</a>; they <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="rigged the Credit Default Swap market (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/o/vQCLP/https://web.archive.org/web/20190908140109/https://haraldhau.com/The_Man_Who_Crashed_the_World.pdf" target="_blank">rigged the Credit Default Swap market</a>; they <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="rigged the mortgage market (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.rollingstone.com/politics/politics-news/the-9-billion-witness-meet-jpmorgan-chases-worst-nightmare-242414/" target="_blank">rigged the mortgage market</a>; they <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="rigged initial public offerings (opens in a new tab)" href="http://www.iposecuritieslitigation.com/amended.php3" target="_blank">rigged initial public offerings</a>; <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="they rig analyst ratings (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2003/04/29/business/wall-street-settlement-overview-10-wall-st-firms-reach-settlement-analyst.html" target="_blank">they rig analyst ratings</a>; they've practically rigged <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="every market in existence (opens in a new tab)" href="https://interactiveswingtrades.com/scandals/" target="_blank">every market in existence</a>.  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":31} -->
<p style="font-size:31px"><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><em>Wanna know something funny? <br></em><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><em>It's already happened..<br></em><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:olympus-google-fonts/google-fonts {"blockType":"h1","fontID":"georgia","fontSize":50,"align":"center","content":"\u003cem\u003eBanana Republic\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e"} /-->

<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":36699,"width":697,"height":931,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/photo-1523060451265-564282bcc107.jpg?fit=768%2C1024&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-36699" width="697" height="931"/></figure></div>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":40,"className":"cursive-background-image"} -->
<p style="font-size:40px" class="cursive-background-image">IN THE COURT OF CHANCERY OF THE STATE OF DELAWARE<br>IN RE DOLE FOOD COMPANY, INC. STOCKHOLDER LITIGATION<br><br><em>"There were <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">36,793,758 shares in the class</span></strong>. At the conclusion of the claims process, however, <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">claimants had submitted facially valid claims for 49,164,415 shares</span></strong>".<br></em><br>....."<em>Despite diligent efforts, the settlement administrator and class<span style="text-decoration: underline;"> <strong>counsel could not resolve the discrepancy</strong></span>".<br></em><br>"<em>Dole held a special meeting of stockholders on October 31, 2013. <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>A narrow majority of 50.9% of the disinterested shares voted in favor</strong></span>, 21.2% voted against, 10.5% abstained, and 17.4% did not vote. The transaction closed on November 1, 2013</em>"<br><br>Vice Chancellor Laster, Memorandum Opinion</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34765,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/d14D5a.xct8n.d.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-09-17-19-47-853.jpg?fit=1024%2C515&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34765"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>During the financial crisis, David Murdock was in deep on debts. After a leveraged buy-out of Dole Foods, years of philanthropic projects, and the recent completion of his Westlake Wellness Center -- a 700 000 square foot luxury hotel directly across the road from Dole's Corporate headquarters -- it was beginning to look like he had finally stretched his finances close to the breaking point.<br><br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":40,"className":"cursive-background-image-3"} -->
<p style="font-size:40px" class="cursive-background-image-3"><em>(<a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="APRIL 9, 2008, LA Times (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2008-apr-09-fi-dole9-story.html" target="_blank">APRIL 9, 2008, LA Times</a>) "The asset sales may relieve pressure on 84-year-old billionaire Chairman David Murdock to make an emergency cash infusion into the Westlake Village-based company. Credit-default swaps suggest a<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> 74% chance of default in the next five years, according to a JPMorgan Chase &amp; Co. valuation model</span></strong>". </em><br><em><br></em><a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="https://archive.is/etRGC#selection-1889.0-1892.0 (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/etRGC#selection-1889.0-1892.0" target="_blank">https://archive.is/etRGC#selection-1889.0-1892.0</a><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>At the time, the high risk bond market had practically frozen, causing many of his loans to go into default.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34519,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-08-22-27-15-491.jpg?fit=1024%2C453&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34519"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Fortunately for him, he had formed long term relationships with some of his lenders, so they decided to come to his rescue.  </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":33892,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-05-12-18-26-415.jpg?fit=1024%2C402&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-33892"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>But the terms were far from favorable.  Pictured below is a snapshot from one of those agreements.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":33976,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dsvrp.s5Pg.htm#7z0" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-05-20-42-52-519.jpg?fit=1024%2C179&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-33976"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>13.87% interest on $349,903,000.. that's $48 000 000 per year...<br><br>Over a 5 year period, this would equate to $240 000 000, and this was just one of several notes..<br><br>Just to put that into perspective, a Bank of America Travel Rewards Card charges  17.24%!</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34022,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2019-07-07-18-00-18-766.jpg?fit=1024%2C423&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34022"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":33983,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dsvr4.s1Jqt.htm?Find=8%2E625%25&amp;Line=42680#Line42680" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-05-22-40-16-505.jpg?fit=1024%2C212&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-33983"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The note was secured by his newly built Westlake Wellbeing hotel.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34031,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dsvrp.s5Pg.a.htm?Find=%22Unrestricted%20Wellbeing%20Joint%20Ventures%22&amp;Line=12283#Line12283" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-06-04-00-10-555.jpg?fit=1024%2C400&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34031"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":40871,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://archive.is/p3yz2" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/interactiveswingtrading.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/bandicam-2020-03-07-15-11-48-774.jpg?fit=1024%2C472&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-40871"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":40872,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://archive.is/p3yz2" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/interactiveswingtrading.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/bandicam-2020-03-07-15-10-42-593.jpg?fit=1024%2C482&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-40872"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":40873,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://archive.is/8Lwge" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/interactiveswingtrading.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/bandicam-2020-03-07-15-10-10-526.jpg?fit=1024%2C482&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-40873"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p> It was located right across the road from Doles's corporate headquarters.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":40,"className":"cursive-background-image-3"} -->
<p style="font-size:40px" class="cursive-background-image-3">(August 30, 2007) "Bond investors may wish Murdock would spend less time on his health crusade and more improving Dole's bottom line. Last year, the company lost $89 million on $6.2 billion in sales. The assessment of its $2.4 billion in bonds and bank debt by Fitch Ratings ranges from "speculative" to "high default risk.".  <br><br>--<em><a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/zYjwi#selection-477.0-484.0" target="_blank">Bloomberg</a></em><br>http://the.honoluluadvertiser.com/article/2007/Aug/30/bz/hawaii708300347.html</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":40,"className":"cursive-background-image-3"} -->
<p style="font-size:40px" class="cursive-background-image-3"><em>"Moody's expects leverage to remain high in support of Mr. Murdock's strategic initiatives, such as construction of a wellness center and acquisition of other food product lines with perceived health benefits". <br></em><br>--<a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Moody's (opens in a new tab)" href="https://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:JJMaEwwQXQ4J:https://www.moodys.com/research/MOODYS-ASSIGNS-Ba3-TO-DOLES-PROPOSED-CREDIT-FACILITIES-AFFIRMS-B1--PR_94590&amp;hl=en&amp;gl=ca&amp;strip=1&amp;vwsrc=0" target="_blank">Moody's</a><br><a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" href="https://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:JJMaEwwQXQ4J:https://www.moodys.com/research/MOODYS-ASSIGNS-Ba3-TO-DOLES-PROPOSED-CREDIT-FACILITIES-AFFIRMS-B1--PR_94590&amp;hl=en&amp;gl=ca&amp;strip=1&amp;vwsrc=0" target="_blank">https://archive.is/xAthi#selection-1543.184-1543.395</a><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>To deal with the crushing debt load, Dole Foods was forced to sell several large assets in 2008/09.  </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":30,"className":"cursive-background-image-3"} -->
<p style="font-size:30px" class="cursive-background-image-3"> (10-K’ for 1/3/09)<br><em>"<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Dole set a goal of selling $200 million in non-core or underperforming assets </strong></span>in 2008, which we have exceeded. During 2008, cash consideration related to our asset sale program totaled approximately $236 million, including <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>sales of land in Hawaii, our fresh-cut flowers headquarters building in Miami, Florida, our citrus and pistachio operations in California, two farms in Chile, a land parcel in Turkey, two older refrigerated ships, a distribution facility in Europe, our JP Fresh and Dole France subsidiaries, and additional acreage located in California. </strong></span>For 2009, we have set a target of $200 million in asset sales. On January 29, 2009, Dole announced progress on our asset sale program. First, Dole closed the first phase of the sale of our flowers division. With the closing of the first phase, Dole completed the sale of our flowers business and retains only certain real estate of the former flowers division to be sold in the subsequent phases of the transaction. Second, Dole closed on the sale of certain banana properties in Latin America. Third, Dole signed a definitive purchase and sale agreement to sell certain property in North America. The sale closed during March 2009. Dole received net cash proceeds of approximately $83 million from these three transactions. When all phases of the transactions are complete, net proceeds to Dole will be approximately $130 million. The cash proceeds will be used to pay down Dole’s debt under its senior secured credit facilities and/or to reinvest in the business. Pending reinvestment, cash proceeds will be used to pay down Dole’s revolving credit facility".</em><br><a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/qMt7a#selection-4997.3-5004.0" target="_blank">https://archive.is/qMt7a#selection-4997.3-5004.0</a><br>https://www.secinfo.com/dR7Km.s92.htm</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>He was even considering selling the entire company at one point. </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":33899,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-05-12-25-02-898.jpg?fit=1024%2C154&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-33899"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>But because the economy was so weak at that time,  finding buyers wasn't as easy as it was before the financial crisis, so he was forced to sell equity interests instead, offering 41% of the company to the public at a price of  $12.50 per share.  </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":33900,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-05-12-26-50-718.jpg?fit=1024%2C144&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-33900"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Headstrong, stubborn, but still full of energy at the ripe age of 86, he liked being the boss, and he wasn't the type to be taking orders from other people.  It was even said that he preferred to be addressed simply as "Chairman" at the company board meetings.  </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":33911,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-05-12-54-31-524.jpg?fit=1024%2C400&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-33911"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>He definitely earned that title, though, going from fighting in World War 2 and later homelessness, to becoming one of the richest people in the world.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":33914,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_H._Murdock" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://interactiveswingtrades.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-05-12-57-52-261.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-33914"/></a></figure></div>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p> He was your prototypical example of an American business magnet.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":29,"className":"cursive-background-image-3"} -->
<p style="font-size:29px" class="cursive-background-image-3">(<a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Bloomberg (opens in a new tab)" href="http://the.honoluluadvertiser.com/article/2007/Aug/30/bz/hawaii708300347.html" target="_blank">Bloomberg</a>)<em>"Murdock keeps a close watch on all of his far-flung real estate, racking up some <strong>200,000 miles a year on his Bombardier Global Express corporate jet</strong>. Among his staff he is known for his attention to every detail".</em><br><a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://archive.is/zYjwi" target="_blank">https://archive.is/zYjwi</a><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The company's IPO prospectus was so long  that if you had tried to scroll through the entire page, it probably would've have taken you 5 minutes straight..  </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

