<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":41040,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/interactiveswingtrades.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/bandicam-2020-03-08-16-02-00-375.jpg?fit=1024%2C467&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-41040"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34099,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dsvrp.s5Pg.a.htm?Find=%22Unrestricted%20Wellbeing%20Joint%20Ventures%22&amp;Line=12283#Line12283" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-07-00-26-15-361.jpg?fit=1024%2C398&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34099"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34033,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-06-10-17-51-470.jpg?fit=1024%2C401&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34033"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34035,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dsvrp.s5Pg.b.htm?Find=%22Westlake%22&amp;Line=16174#Line16174" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-06-10-25-27-873.jpg?fit=1024%2C400&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34035"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":37762,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dsvrp.s5Pg.b.htm?Find=%22Westlake%22&amp;Line=16174#Line16174" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-22-21-40-37-829.jpg?fit=1024%2C418&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-37762"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":35781,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dsvrp.s5Pg.b.htm?Find=%22Westlake%22&amp;Line=14859#Line14859" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-13-18-27-35-755.jpg?fit=1024%2C376&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-35781"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><br>But he still hadn't fully paid off the rest of his debts connected to the hotel, and this is where you begin to see the banks come into the picture.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":33954,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dsvr4.s1Jqt.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-05-15-24-33-819.jpg?fit=1024%2C505&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-33954"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>In order for Mr.Murdock to pay off the hotel, he would've been forced to sell his controlling interest in the company.  But the banks liked Murdock, so they facilitated a transaction that was able to solve this problem.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34866,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-05-00-31-59-551.jpg?fit=1024%2C323&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34866"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The transaction allowed him and his partners -- the banks -- to maintain a controlling interest in this massive 150 year old company.<br><br>At the time, Dole Foods represented 1/4 of all banana sales worldwide; 131,000 acres of farms and other land holdings; six modern corrugated box manufacturing plants in Latin America and Asia; the largest dedicated refrigerated containerized fleet in the world representing 14,800 refrigerated containers, and 11 owned and 13 chartered vessels.  In short, this was an empire, and you don't just give something like that up easily.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>To keep Murdock in power, they set up an off-balance sheet entity called "<em>MACES Trust</em>", and the deal was that his creditors  would hold on to the stock and use it as collateral for a loan.  Now that the company was public, it was easier to sell this ownership interest, whereas before, finding a buyer could be a long and arduous process.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><br><br><br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":35118,"width":958,"height":448,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-10-23-04-24-702.jpg?fit=1024%2C479&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-35118" width="958" height="448"/></figure></div>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":33991,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-05-23-55-10-793.jpg?fit=1024%2C454&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-33991"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"blue-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="blue-yellow-background-link">Contrary to what most people might naturally suspect, these banks were much more than just Mr. Murdock's disinterested lenders, and not only did this come out in <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="court documents (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.ph/Bopce" target="_blank">court documents</a>, but it is also clearly displayed on their balance sheet.<br><br>Just take a look at all the interest Mr. Murdock was being forced to pay these banks.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34554,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dVut2.6D3u.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-08-23-59-55-875.jpg?fit=1024%2C460&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34554"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34553,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dRqWm.4fDQy.htm#2421" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-09-00-00-32-423.jpg?fit=1024%2C460&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34553"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34548,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-08-23-48-30-060.jpg?fit=1024%2C500&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34548"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34549,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-08-23-49-41-789.jpg?fit=1024%2C396&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34549"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>This was Mr. Murdock's ownership percentage before the leveraged buyout. As you can see, it was only 23%. <br><br>10-K for 2002, filed on Wednesday, 3/26/03, at 8:08am ET</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34550,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-08-23-50-09-412.jpg?fit=1024%2C475&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34550"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>In 2007, the interest payment practically doubles, almost touching $200 million.<br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34551,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dR7Km.u9g.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-08-23-51-02-365.jpg?fit=1024%2C475&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34551"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"red-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="red-yellow-background-link">Let's not forget, this is on no capital intensive work or investment whatsoever. Yes, it costs money to run a bank, but nothing like running Dole Foods, the largest producer of fresh produce in the world.<br><br>There is a lot of work, a lot more risk, and hell of a lot more blood, sweat, and tears that goes into bringing the world their fresh produce. As it was noted before, Mr. Murdock clocked 200 km on his corporate jet on any given year, and as to the workers <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="toiling his fields (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/bylTv#selection-1587.0-1592.0" target="_blank">toiling his fields</a> in those overseas plantations, God only knows how many back breaking steps they had to take in the hot sun just to bring us that fresh fruit. Compared to this -- along with the shipping, planning, training, and all the manpower that goes into Dole -- the banks did virtually nothing for this money.  <br><br>You don't think his creditors wanted to keep Mr. Murdock in power? They still had a lot of money on the line, and there's nothing that a lender hates more than uncertainty.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34552,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dsvr4.rrjf.htm#csxk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-08-23-51-41-320.jpg?fit=1024%2C475&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34552"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Notice how you never see the "or loss" sign beside the interest payments?<br><br>Lloyd Blankfein once claimed that banks do "<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.reuters.com/article/us-goldmansachs-blankfein/goldman-sachs-boss-says-banks-do-gods-work-idUSTRE5A719520091108" target="_blank">God's work</a>, so maybe this is just their modest remittance for being burdened with such a great responsibility.<br><br>Who knows..The lord works in <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20130301115039/https://www.activistpost.com/2013/01/goldman-sachs-made-400-million-betting.html" target="_blank">mysterious ways </a>, as they say. </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image -->
<figure class="wp-block-image"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-06-00-00-30-470.jpg?fit=1024%2C232&amp;ssl=1" alt="This image has an empty alt attribute; its file name is bandicam-2020-02-06-00-00-30-470.jpg"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The deal was that he would transfer ownership of the stock -- again, 27% of the great Dole Food company, founded June 2, 1851, 168 years ago -- on<strong> </strong>November 1st, 2012, which you see happening in the snapshot below.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":33956,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/d14sr8.p1yJ5.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-05-15-28-27-380.jpg?fit=1024%2C486&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-33956"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":33967,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-05-16-01-44-917.jpg?fit=1024%2C345&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-33967"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>This is from his first 13-D following the IPO.  It again shows the parties to the "Trust" offering -- "<em>MACES Trust</em> ".</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":37810,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dsvr4.s1R1y.8.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-22-23-59-50-430.jpg?fit=1024%2C299&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-37810"/></a></figure></div>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The creditors transferred the money in exchange for the collateral at one of <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Sullivan and Cromwell's (opens in a new tab)" href="https://theintercept.com/2018/01/30/jay-clayton-sec-donald-trump-wall-street/" target="_blank">Sullivan and Cromwell's</a> offices in Los Angeles. </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34192,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dsvr4.s1R1y.8.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-07-15-34-25-473.jpg?fit=1024%2C535&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34192"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>They even felt the need to specify that delivery of the stock did not constitute as a payment of interest.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34195,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dsvr4.s1R1y.8.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-07-15-44-32-228.jpg?fit=1024%2C404&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34195"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>And you can see here that he paid down a large portion of that debt with the proceeds of the "Trust" offering.  </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"width":1450,"height":460} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image is-resized"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dsvr4.s1wHe.htm?Find=%222014%20Notes%22&amp;Line=256#Line256" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-07-01-53-06-643.jpg?fit=1024%2C326&amp;ssl=1" alt="This image has an empty alt attribute; its file name is bandicam-2020-02-07-01-53-06-643.jpg" width="1450" height="460"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>This was one the original notes issued in connection with the leveraged buyout; the same note he paid down with the IPO proceeds. </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34583,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dR7Km.21Gy.htm#1ooq" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-09-02-04-29-594.jpg?fit=1024%2C366&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34583"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Listed below are the buyers of one these notes, or to put it simply, the banks that loaned Mr. Murdock the money. <br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34579,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://archive.is/VWztS#selection-4745.175-4745.194" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-09-01-59-28-798.jpg?fit=1024%2C366&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34579"/></a><figcaption>https://www.secinfo.com/dR7Km.21Gy.d.htm</figcaption></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>It was the same day Mr. Murdock took the company private.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34575,"width":1450,"height":218,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dR7Km.21Gy.htm#1ooq" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-09-01-27-01-774.jpg?fit=1024%2C154&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34575" width="1450" height="218"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34592,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dR7Km.2pj.d.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-09-02-16-54-460.jpg?fit=1024%2C409&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34592"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>But back to "MACES Trust".   <br><br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34858,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dsvr4.s1Jqt.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-09-20-30-39-408.jpg?fit=1024%2C461&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34858"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Why would someone pay $21 million for IOU certificates ("<em>THE MACES</em> ") secured by those pledged shares in the trust? And why does this "Trust" offering provide an option to buy an extra 3 600 000 shares? That's virtually indistinguishable from an over allotment-option. Why would they feel the need to offer an over allotment option for shares that are not even going to be registered?<br><br>What is going on here?</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Let's take a step back.  <br><br>Who really owns this company? <br><br>Is it Mr. Murdock?</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34550,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://interactiveswingtrades.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-08-23-50-09-412-1024x475.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-34550"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>That was his ownership before the merger: only 23%.  <br><br>So where did the other 3/4's come from?  It didn't just appear out of nowhere.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34874,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/dR7Km.21gh.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-09-21-25-15-042.jpg?fit=1024%2C382&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34874"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>You can see in snapshot above that the majority of the shares were purchased with borrowed money.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":34878,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img src="https://interactiveswingtrades.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-08-23-51-41-320-1.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-34878"/></figure></div>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>After careful analysis, you will also see that the majority of the earnings from this massive fruit empire actually went to the banks, and not Mr.Murdock.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>In fact, when you add up all the interest payments from 1998-2009, you end up with $1.6 billion..</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Guess how much net income Dole Food's and Mr.Murdock generated over that same time period?</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Only $630 million!</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Yes, the banks were making almost triple the net income that Dole was making.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"blue-yellow-background-link"} -->
<p class="blue-yellow-background-link">Unfortunately, we will never know who owns all these promissory notes because debt securities are typically not subject to the same beneficial ownership reporting rules as equities. Banks usually buy promissory notes so they can sell them to other people -- usually their depositors -- so for all we know, it could be Lord Rothschild himself that could own all those notes, and we would have no way of actually knowing.  Hey, you never know -- 52% of the equities are controlled by only<a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20200220020514/https://interactiveswingtrades.com/2019/12/09/52-of-equities-are-held-by-the-top-1-of-the-population-fred/"> 1% of the population</a>; 35% of which is owned by <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20200220020257/https://interactiveswingtrades.com/2019/12/13/foreign-investors-own-about-35-percent-of-u-s-corporate-stock/" target="_blank">foreign investors</a>.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Are you starting to understand how the system works?  Technically nobody actually knew who was taking in the majority of the profits from the largest fresh produce manufacturing company in the world; a company representing 1/4th of all banana sales WORLDWIDE.<br><br>If you own a company, but you only receive 1/3rd of the profits (after paying for all expenses, INCLUDING taxes), who is the real owner? <br><br><br><br><em> </em><br><br><br><em>Not you..<br></em><br><br><br><br><br><br><br></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

