<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Mr. Murdock  and his banking partners did eventually land that sale they were looking for.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34217,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://interactiveswingtrades.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-07-17-33-11-402-1024x376.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-34217"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>And the proceeds were used to pay off their debts.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34905,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-09-22-58-37-582.jpg?fit=1024%2C301&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34905"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>But he was forced to give up Asia to the Japanese.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":38679,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/d14D5a.pEExt.htm?Find=%22%241%2E3%20billion%20reduction%22&amp;Line=903#Line903" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-26-11-40-22-626.jpg?fit=1024%2C405&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-38679"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Good timing. You can see in the snapshot pictured below that the record date was only 6 days before he was set to lose his controlling interest. Remember, he was due to transfer ownership of that 27% stake to his "<em>creditors</em> " on November.1st.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34897,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/d14D5a.pEExt.htm?Find=%22DB%20Private%20Clients%22&amp;Line=5585#Line5585" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-09-22-46-49-313.jpg?fit=1024%2C451&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34897"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>And you can see here that he no longer had a controlling interest in the company.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34901,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/d14D5a.pDmp4.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-09-22-51-09-467.jpg?fit=1024%2C394&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34901"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Then something miraculous occurred: he somehow managed to buy back the company only one year later!</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34941,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.secinfo.com/d14D5a.xcfP1.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-10-00-04-12-679.jpg?fit=1024%2C362&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34941"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>And he only had to pay $1.00 more than the IPO price!</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":34944,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://i1.wp.com/stocktrades.exchange/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bandicam-2020-02-10-00-13-59-578.jpg?fit=1024%2C437&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-34944"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>After fighting to remain in control during the worst financial crisis since the great depression; offering to sell the whole company for as low as $700 million; and setting up this unusual trust entity that allowed him and his bankers to initiate a sort of unregistered mini off-balance sheet side-deal -- strange IPO beside the real IPO kind of transaction ("<em>MACES Trust</em> "); all the while demanding to be addressed simply as "Chairman" at the company board meetings, he then sold his controlling interest, but miraculously bought back the company one year later, AND he got to keep the Wellness Center??</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>That's one heck of a deal, don't you think?</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>You might also be wondering how he was able to buy it back so easily. Don't worry, you're not alone on that front, because soon after the deal closed, he was <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://archive.is/7Yeja#selection-2007.0-2014.0" target="_blank">quickly sued</a> by a consortium of activist investors. One of them bought 8.3% of the outstanding capital stock only a few weeks before the vote for the sole purpose of filing a suit!<br><br>It was even claimed that his <em>"creditors"</em> (partners) privately believed the company was worth <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://archive.is/t7b2C#selection-4545.0-4548.0" target="_blank">$23 per share</a>, and after all was said and done, the settlement eventually went on to become one of the largest appraisals in Delaware's 118 year history as a corporate tax haven.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:separator {"className":"cursive-background-image-2"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator cursive-background-image-2"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"customFontSize":40,"className":"cursive-background-image-2"} -->
<p style="font-size:40px" class="cursive-background-image-2"><em>(<a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="WSJ, Nov. 22, 2013 2:31 pm ET (opens in a new tab)" href="https://archive.is/psAuQ" target="_blank">Wall Street Journal, Nov. 22, 2013</a>) "In all, holders of nearly 14 million shares, more than 25% of all Dole shares not owned before the buyout by CEO David Murdock, are seeking more money in court. That makes Dole's <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">one of the largest appraisals ever in Delaware</span></strong>, where most such suits are brought, according to a review of court filings".</em></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

